metadata.name: Valley of Empty Future #57
metadata.description:
*translated from drone swarm operator 51b13*
Preliminary analysis of the planet's atmosphere suggest an increased concentration of carbon monoxide, consistent with temperature readings.
No fauna or flora detected on immediate surface. Even though soil spectroscopy confirm presence of organic compounds, samples must be collected in order to have definitive results.

Scouts have confirmed, trough x-ray and radar imaging, sprawling areas of artificial environments. High density of buildings suggest an intricate and highly developed societal structure, with only it's tallest buildings piercing trough the meters deep silicate dust covering most of the area. It intrigues me why build so high, would these be religious monuments to be seen by all, for their exuberance? Immediately forwarding digital reconstruction of the -cities?- for Cosmic Sociologists to further speculate on their purposes.

////

On fullscreen view, press P to download a 1920*2560 PNG

Made in Cables.gl

metadata.name: Arrows Between Emotions #22
metadata.description:
The project “Arrows Between Emotions” was formed with a concern to present this transformation in an artist and code developer, making the logic appear through precise and well-defined forms, but that the stage was really of emotions through freer curves involving aligned with accentuated movements in directions of straight or oblique ascents and even in more circular or decadent processes that are part of the journey of the wheel of life of art and the artist.


The process of the work involved the construction of a background to receive the shapes and colors. I used an algorithm that generated a distribution of noise across the screen, with its coloring related to the shapes in the search for a pleasant composition. Then came the objective forms, setting the stage, finally, for the flow of emotions through the agglutinated and dispersed curves soaked in colors in a game of shadow and light, presenting the depth and movement of the creation process and the orientation to which it takes. all the strength of this walk.

Press 's' key in live mode to save in png.

metadata.name: Boids 2D #167
metadata.description:
'Boids 2D' is a Generative Token that represent the flocking of birds over a landscape. The name 'Boids' comes from a famous computer animation / simulation program.

The landscape is rendered as a texture using a kind of warped noise as height map.

The boids are disposed along the flow lines obtained from the noise gradient. This gives the sensation that the Boids follow the undulations of the landscape.

Previously embedded in the 'Boids' (3D) Generative Token as an ester egg on 20% of iterations, now every iterations will be 2D as viewed from the sky.

Every owner of the 'Boids' (3D) GT will receive one 'Boids 2D' for free. The owner that minted a 'Boids' with ester egg will receive two 'Boids 2D' for free.

It is possible to save a 1600x1600 png with key 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape an the landscape and Boids flock (combined on a single number on the features).
- 21 color mapping for landscape and Boids.
- Two kind of border, solid or negative.

Features:
Palette: color palette name (21 different palettes)
NoiseControl: noise control parameter (0 - 15)
Border: the border can be in solid color or negative color (Solid, Negative)


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Secunda #50
Love #138
metadata.description:
We all experience love at different scales, ranging from scarcely perceived instances of kindness to unforgettable affections shown to us by family and friends, pets and partners. Each of these moments link us to the same boundless and enveloping interconnectedness that persists across space and time: the infinite source of our deepest aspirations.

Like the feeling of simple bliss, ‘Love’ portrays the visceral radiant light and warmth of our innermost joys. By taking a moment to open ourselves up, these swirling worlds of weightless and seemingly infinite brush strokes invite us to slow down and dwell in prismatic intuitive swells.

In doing so, we may find the immense and omnipresent love that needs only our awareness to be felt.

__________

Press 1-9 to load at different scales (1 = 2,000x2,000 (default), 9 = 10,000x10,000)
When zoomed in, once the output is fully loaded, you can click and drag to move around the canvas
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'B' to toggle the background texture on or off
Press 'A' to toggle the loading animation (recommended for very large scales)

metadata.name: redline #196
metadata.description:
This is my second generative art project on fxhash. I wanted a project that offered more VARIETY compared for my first project so this is what I came up with: a clean and simple rectangles & lines project :D 

There are a few options for the number of columns that are generated: 3, 5, 7, 9, and each column is randomly filled with dense or alternating line patterns (sometimes no pattern!). 3 columns are common, the rest are less common. Having more than half the columns empty is relatively rare. Having all columns empty is extremely rare! 

Also I have to give credit to Tyler Hobbs, this piece was super inspired by an old IG post of his. Please enjoy!

metadata.name: Secunda #21
Glimpse Of Draeconian Epidermis & Tapestry #72
metadata.description:
Discover the artistic style and bold fashion of your favorite Reptilian overlords, the *Draeconians*!

Those NFTs are pictures, sure, but more intricately they are *Glimpses* of what these magnificent scaled shapeshifters are able to create using their sophisticated *Epidermis* machinery.

Nevertheless, and as it is the case for some humans in our world, you'll probably notice eventually that more often than not, the output products are better suited to be used as *Tapestry* rather than clothes or skin...

Features:
- 42 palettes aka Pigmentore's Names
- 4 rendering techniques aka Workore's Names
- 5 types of patterns aka Designore's Tribes...
- ... which result into more than 40 different patterns aka Designore's Names
- 5 transformations aka Designore's Traits
- etc.

About me:
I am MaKRz, a creative coder and generative artist living in Lisbon area. I like to take inspiration in real life and nature (animals, landscapes, buildings) to start with a concept and eventually totally mess it up.
Check out @MaKRz666 on Twitter.

Made with p5js
